metadata.text: Melanie: Why are you late?
metadata.context: [Rebecca riding bus and then running into a school. Meets up with Melanie]

metadata.text: Rebecca: You’re not going to like the answer.
metadata.context: [Rebecca riding bus and then running into a school. Meets up with Melanie]

metadata.text: Melanie: I already know the answer.
metadata.context: [Rebecca riding bus and then running into a school. Meets up with Melanie]

metadata.text: Rebecca: I missed the bus.
metadata.context: [Rebecca riding bus and then running into a school. Meets up with Melanie]

metadata.text: Melanie: I don’t doubt it, no bus stops near Brad’s. You spent the night, the alarm didn’t work. Or maybe it did.
metadata.context: [Rebecca riding bus and then running into a school. Meets up with Melanie]

metadata.text: Rebecca: I didn’t sleep with him.
metadata.context: [Rebecca riding bus and then running into a school. Meets up with Melanie]

metadata.text: Rebecca: I missed the bus!
metadata.context: Melanie: Girl, there’s...[Interrupted]

metadata.text: Melanie: There’s something either very wrong with you, or there’s something very wrong with him.

metadata.text: Rebecca: There’s nothing wrong with him.
metadata.context: Melanie: Girl, there’s...[Interrupted]

metadata.text: Melanie: Please tell me you know that for a fact.

metadata.context: Melanie: Girl, there’s...[Interrupted]

metadata.text: Wilson: 29 year old female, first seizure one month ago, lost the ability to speak. Babbled like a baby. Present deterioration of mental status.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: See that? They all assume I’m a patient because of this cane.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: So put on a white coat like the rest of us.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: I don’t want them to think I’m a doctor.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: You see where the administration might have a problem with that attitude.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: People don’t want a sick doctor.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: Fair enough. I don’t like healthy patients. The 29 year old female…
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: The one who can’t talk, I liked that part.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: She’s my cousin.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: And your cousin doesn’t like the diagnosis. I wouldn’t either. Brain tumor, she’s gonna die, boring.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: No wonder you’re such a renowned diagnostician. You don’t need to actually know anything to figure out what’s wrong.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: You’re the oncologist; I’m just a lowly infectious disease guy.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: Hah, yes, just a simple country doctor. Brain tumors at her age are highly unlikely.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: She’s 29. Whatever she’s got is highly unlikely.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: Protein markers for the three most prevalent brain cancers came up negative.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: That’s an HMO lab; you might as well have sent it to a high school kid with a chemistry set.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: No family history.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: I thought your uncle died of cancer.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: Other side. No environmental factors.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: That you know of.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: And she’s not responding to radiation treatment.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: House: None of which is even close to dispositive. All it does is raise one question. Your cousin goes to an HMO?
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]

metadata.text: Wilson: Come on! Why leave all the fun for the coroner? What’s the point of putting together a team if you’re not going to use them? You’ve got three overqualified doctors working for you. Getting bored.
metadata.context: [House and Wilson are walking through the hallway. All you can see is their hands and legs, showing that House is using a cane and limping. Wilson is the only one of the two wearing a lab coat.]
